O life, thou art a song of endless grace,  
A dawn that wakes the sleeping earth and sky,  
Where blossoms blush and rivers softly trace  
The path of time with gentle, golden eye.  
I love thy breath, the wind that stirs the trees,  
The laugh of children, bright and free,  
The stars that burn with ancient, silent ease—  
Each moment sings a truth I cannot see.  
Thy storms may rage, thy night may be profound,  
Yet still, I dwell in hope, in joy, in fire.  
For every breath, a gift, a fleeting crown,  
And in thy dance, I find my soul’s desire.  
So let me live, and love, and walk with thee—  
For life, my love, is all that ever is.
